        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 10:30AM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 1029 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Edgecomb, or near Surf City, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and frequent lightning. Torrential
rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Surf City, Topsail Beach, Topsail, Woodside, and Edgecomb.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building. Do not
drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
